Healing Properties
Prehnite is considered a stone of unconditional love and the crystal to heal the healer.  It enhances precognition and inner knowing.  Enables you always to be prepared.  Prehnite calms the environment and brings peace and protection.  It teaches how to be in harmony with nature and the elemental forces. Mineral Description
Prehnite is an inosilicate of calcium and aluminium and crystallizes most often forms as stalactitic or botryoidal shapes. Prehnite is named after an 18th century Dutch colonel, Hendrik Von Prehn, who discovered it, and in fact is one of the first minerals to be named after a historical person.

The color of Prehnite is mostly green, yellow, or it can be transparent. Its unique shades are not likely to be seen in any other mineral.

The main locality of Prehnite is in South Africa. Some deposits are also found in Australia, China, India and the USA.
